While reviewing impact for bug 27546 (To see if other flush operations exhibited
the same behaviour) I found the following code in ZipOutputStream:


    /**
     * Flushes this output stream and forces any buffered output bytes
     * to be written out to the stream.
     *
     * @exception  IOException  if an I/O error occurs.
     * @since 1.14
     */
    public void flush() throws IOException {
        if (out == null) {
            out.flush();
        }
    }

Which will not flush if a stream is attached, and throw a NullPointerException
if no stream is attached.

